adjust_ohlc             Adjust the first four columns of _OHLC_ data
                        using the "adjusted" price column.
calc_endpoints          Calculate a vector of equally spaced end points
                        along the elements of a vector, matrix, or time
                        series.
calc_sharpe             Calculate the Sharpe and Sortino ratios of a
                        time series of returns.
calc_skew               Calculate the skewness or kurtosis of a time
                        series of returns.
chart_dygraph           Plot an interactive _dygraphs_ candlestick plot
                        with background shading for an _OHLC_ time
                        series in _xts_ format.
chart_dygraph2y         Plot an interactive _dygraphs_ line plot for
                        two _xts_ time series, with two _"y"_ axes.
chart_xts               Plot either a line plot or a candlestick plot
                        of an _xts_ time series, with custom line
                        colors, y-axis range, and with vertical
                        background shading.
chart_xts2y             Plot two _xts_ time series with two y-axes in
                        an x11 window.
diffit                  Calculate the row differences of a _numeric_ or
                        _Boolean_ vector, matrix, or _xts_ time series.
diffohlc                Calculate the reduced form of an _OHLC_ time
                        series, or calculate the standard form from the
                        reduced form of an _OHLC_ time series.
diffxts                 Calculate the time differences of an _xts_ time
                        series.
do_call                 Recursively apply a function to a list of
                        objects, such as _xts_ time series.
do_call_assign          Apply a function to a list of objects, merge
                        the outputs into a single object, and assign
                        the object to the output environment.
do_call_rbind           Recursively "rbind" a list of objects, such as
                        _xts_ time series.
etf_data                The etf_data dataset contains a single
                        environment called etfenv, which includes daily
                        'OHLC' time series data for a portfolio of
                        symbols.  All the prices are already adjusted.
get_col                 Extract columns of data from _OHLC_ time series
                        using column field names.
get_data                Load _OHLC_ time series data into an
                        environment, either from an external source
                        (download from _YAHOO_), or from _CSV_ files in
                        a local drive.
get_name                Extract symbol names (tickers) from a vector of
                        _character_ strings.
getpoly                 Download an _OHLC_ time series of prices from
                        Polygon.
lagit                   Apply a lag to a _numeric_ or _Boolean_ vector,
                        matrix, or _xts_ time series.
lagxts                  Apply a time lag to an _xts_ time series.
nalocf                  Replace 'NA' values with the most recent
                        non-'NA' values prior to them.
optim_bfgs              Perform multivariate optimization using the
                        BFGS method.
optim_coordescent       Perform multivariate optimization using
                        coordinate descent with quasi-Newton updates.
optim_newton            Perform one-dimensional optimization using the
                        Newton-Raphson method.
plot_acf                Calculate the autocorrelation function (ACF) of
                        a time series of returns, and plot it.
roll_max                Calculate the rolling maximum of an _xts_ time
                        series over a sliding window (lookback period).
roll_sum                Calculate the rolling sum of a _numeric_
                        vector, matrix, or _xts_ time series over a
                        sliding window (lookback period).
sub_set                 Subset an _xts_ time series (extract an _xts_
                        sub-series corresponding to the input dates).
tdistr                  Calculate the density of the non-standard
                        Student's t-distribution.
to_period               Aggregate an _xts_ time series to a lower
                        periodicity.
